  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Integration of Internally Displaced Populations (IDPs) in North-East Nigeria (Shelter/Non-Food Items (NFI))</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the durable solutions (DS) pilot project is to provide an evidence-based model for addressing protracted displacement in north-east Nigeria. The project presents a multi-sectoral and multilevel approach, including shelter &amp; non-food items (NFI), early recovery and livelihoods, water, sanitation and hygiene as well as protection interventions. Durable solutions-oriented interventions in support of displaced populations are implemented following multi-stakeholder consultations including the Government of Nigeria towards the development of a viable durable solutions-strategy to address protracted displacement in north-east Nigeria. Activities supported through CERF focus on life-saving component of DS project. As part of the project funded by CERF, IOM is establishing a settlement in the local community on a land in Borno or Adamawa State in coordination with the State government, local authorities, the Camp Coordination and Camp Management/Shelter/NFI sector, and other stakeholders (community, community leaders etc.), aiming to benefit 1,500 displaced individuals from durable integrated services.</narrative>
  </description>
